      "content": "that's an interesting contrast. i'm curious though, when you say the maori approach is \"organic\" compared to the \"hierarchical\" european style, isn't that kind of a simplification? it almost sounds like you're saying maori systems are less developed or less organized because they aren't centralized. can you explain why you chose those specific terms? i want to make sure the exhibit doesn't come off as patronizing or implying that maori society is less \"advanced\" just because it functions differently.",
